(1/2)-Pakistan is facing a shortage of cotton due to floods resulting in a loss of 3.5mn bales or 36% of the crop with an estimated value of $1.5 bn. The share of textile in exports is 59% & Pakistan needs to import cotton to fulfil industry needs.
